tags: don't say I didn't warn you
summary: First Off I’d like to wish a very Happy Birthday to my favorite Actor and Doctor, David Tennant. I would then like to apologize...
caption:
First Off I’d like to wish a very Happy Birthday to my favorite Actor and Doctor, David Tennant. I would then like to apologize to Carly Simon for butchering her wonderful song. I also apologize to those of you who watch this video for any bleeding of your ears. I am fully aware that I cannot sing and no amount of echoing and reverbing was able to fix that. I can tell you however, that I will never, EVER, make bets over baseball again. I will say though, it is truly the mark of a great friend when they tell you that “embarrassing yourself in immense proportions is not a reason to welch on a bet.” (Thanks Michael, love you too.)

You are welcome to mute the video by all means, it’s still enjoyable to watch all the clips of David without hearing the music. Blimey. Okay, you’ve been officially warned now, so… Enjoy? Lyrics are below. 

Lyrics:

Nobody Does it Better
Makes me feel sad for the rest
Nobody does it half as good as you
David you’re the best

Your roles, the way that you own them
And Oh Yes, you own them
There’s some kind of magic inside you
That brings us all running
So just keep it coming
How’d you learn to do the things you do

Cause Nobody Does it Better
And in my opinion no one could
Nobody does it quite the way you do
you just had to be so good

Good guys and Baddies
Suave Lovers and Daddies
Billionaire Ducks and Snake-eyed Demons
Podcasts Tuesday mornings
New Big Finish stories

We can’t wait to see what you do next.

And Nobody Does it Better
Makes me feel sad for the rest
Nobody does it half as good as you
David you’re the best

*Please do not @ people or make your own additions to this and please keep your comments and opinions in your own tags. Thank you.*

summary: I've never been a fangirl. Really. And I don't think that I'm now. Rather it's sth a little bit ineffable, bc this man's...
body:
I’ve never been a fangirl. Really. And I don’t think that I’m now. Rather it’s sth a little bit ineffable, bc this man’s changing my life. He makes me stronger, more confident. “He makes this world a better place”.

I don’t want to write a long post about my emotions, bc I think all my feelings - just my feelings and people are not interested in them. So all you, guys, should know - I really like David and what he did, does and will do!

Happy birthday, David Tennant!
